        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 7 at 4:34PM EDT by NWS Wakefield VA</headline>
        <description>At 434 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Courtland, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Sedley around 440 PM EDT.
Zuni around 510 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Vicksville, Whitley,
Collosse, Berlin, Walters, Boaz, Sebrell, and Burdette.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Heavy rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
